🪙 Binance Spot Trading Bot

A simple yet extensible Python trading bot built on the Binance Spot Testnet API — perfect for demonstrating algorithmic trading logic, order handling, and error management.

🚀 Features

Connects to Binance Spot Testnet

Executes Market and Limit orders

Supports Buy and Sell actions

Tracks price, PnL, and balance

Implements logging and error handling

Optional auto strategy mode for demo trading

⚙️ Setup Instructions
1️⃣ Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/AvaniVJ/binance.git
cd binance

2️⃣ Create and activate a virtual environment
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate     # Windows
# source venv/bin/activate   # Mac/Linux

3️⃣ Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4️⃣ Create a .env file

In your project root, create a file named .env with the following content:

BINANCE_API_KEY=your_api_key
BINANCE_API_SECRET=your_api_secret
BINANCE_TESTNET_URL=https://testnet.binance.vision
SYMBOL=BTCUSDT
TRADE_QUANTITY=0.001

5️⃣ Run the bot
python a.py

🧾 Logging

All actions, orders, and errors are logged to:

futures_style_bot.log


To view logs live in VS Code:

Open the file

Right-click → “Follow Log” (or “Follow Output”)

🧠 Notes

The bot uses Binance Spot Testnet, not Futures.

Make sure your API keys are from https://testnet.binance.vision
.

Ensure your account has Testnet funds before trading.

